# ai-engineering-harness

This repository uses ai-engineering-harness.

Core harness rules are provider-neutral. This file is the Cursor adapter entrypoint.

## Read Order

Before acting on a harness request:

1. Read `.ai-harness/activation.md`
2. Read `.harness/STATE.md`
3. Read the active session under `.harness/sessions/`
4. Read the relevant Cursor project command in `.cursor/commands/`
5. Read the relevant command contract in `.ai-harness/commands/`
6. Read the matching prompt template in `.ai-harness/prompt-templates/`

## Important

Cursor project install provides native `/harness-*` commands through `.cursor/commands/`.
Use `.cursor/rules/` for guardrails and repository activation, and keep `.ai-harness/runtime-commands/` as the local catalog mirror.

Do not invent slash commands.
Do not use legacy colon-separated command IDs.

Always follow `.ai-harness/agent-system/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md`.

Use the response formats in `.ai-harness/agent-system/RESPONSE_CONTRACT.md`.

Fallback instruction: **Use /harness-plan for this repository.**

